all studies had to be prospective population-based cohort studies. Inherent to the nature of population-based studies this meant that except for a selection criterion of age, no other selection criteria were applied;
cerebral imaging had to be performed (either magnetic resonance imaging [MRI] or computed tomography) for the visualization of white matter hyperintensities, covert brain infarcts, or microbleeds;
All studies had to have investigated the association of any of the three pathologies with the risk of incident all-dementia or AD [Alzheimer's disease.].
